<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <head>No. 65.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName type="to">Schenck</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 28,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>This Government declines to agree to the proposed altering of the
                            supplementary Article. The establishment of the principle embodied
                            therein has been its object in adhering to the presentation of the
                            indirect claims, and its recognition is the inducement for not pressing
                            them before the Tribunal.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>